1. Ownership & Intellectual Property
The source code, logic, JNI bridges, and branding of KodrixIDE are the sole intellectual property of Zohaib.

No Redistribution: You are strictly prohibited from hosting, mirroring, or redistributing this source code on any platform (GitHub, GitLab, etc.) under your own name or brand.

Anti-Plagiarism Protection: You may not "copy-paste" or extract core logic (such as PTY handling or the libgit2 bridge) for use in competing software products.

No Derivative Works: You may not use this code to build, maintain, or distribute a competing Integrated Development Environment (IDE).

2. Usage & Revenue Model
KodrixIDE operates on a "Free for Testing, Paid for Earning" model.

Personal Use: Usage for local development, education, and private testing is Free.

Commercial Trigger: Any public deployment of a service or application powered by KodrixIDE requires a valid Commercial License.

Revenue Clause: If your project generates any revenue (via advertisements, subscriptions, or direct sales), you are legally required to purchase a Commercial License from the author.

3. Mandatory Attribution
Transparency is required for all projects utilizing this software. You must include the following credit in your documentation, "About" section, and README:

"Powered by KodrixIDE by Zohaib"

A direct, clickable link to the original KodrixIDE repository must be maintained at all times.

4. Security & Usage Protections
No Sublicensing: You may not rent, lease, or sell your rights to this software to third parties.

Ethical Use: You may not use KodrixIDE for the development of malware, unauthorized network penetration (hacking), or any activity that violates local or international laws.

No Circumvention: Any attempt to bypass license verification or paywalls within the software results in the immediate and permanent termination of your usage rights.

5. Termination of License
Violation of any terms in this agreement results in the automatic termination of your license. Upon termination, you must:

Cease all use of the software.

Delete all copies of the source code and binaries.

Shut down any active public deployments.

6. Disclaimer of Warranty (The "AS IS" Shield)
THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. THE AUTHOR (ZOHAIB) SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY DATA LOSS, HARDWARE DAMAGE, FINANCIAL LOSS, OR LEGAL ISSUES ARISING FROM THE USE OF THIS SOFTWARE. YOU ASSUME ALL RISK ASSOCIATED WITH THE INSTALLATION AND OPERATION OF KODRIXIDE.

How to implement this "Good Looking" License:
The File: Create a file named exactly LICENSE (no extension) in your root folder. GitHub will automatically give it a special icon and a dedicated sidebar link.

The Header: Use the # symbol for the main title to make it large and bold.

The TL;DR: In your README.md, add this small "Human-Readable" summary so people understand it instantly:

⚖️ License at a Glance

Hobbyists: 100% Free to use and test.

Businesses: If you earn money using this, you must pay.

Developers: No stealing code or building clones.

Credits: You must mention KodrixIDE in your docs.
